children.comment: Everything in Dart is an [Object].
children.name: Object

children.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all [Object]s is to return true if and
only if [:this:] and [other] are the same object.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override
the [hashCode] method as well to maintain consistency.
Returns a string representation of this object.
children.name: toString

children.comment:
[noSuchMethod] is invoked when users invoke a non-existant method
on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the
invocation are passed to [noSuchMethod] in an [Invocation].
If [noSuchMethod] returns a value, that value becomes the result of
the original invocation.

The default behavior of [noSuchMethod] is to throw a
[noSuchMethodError].
children.name: noSuchMethod

children.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the
same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality
operator [:==:]. Other than that there are no guarantees about
the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and
there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides [hashCode] it should override the
equality operator as well to maintain consistency.
children.name: hashCode

children.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.
children.name: runtimeType

children.comment:
Creates a new [Object] instance.

[Object] instances have no meaningful state, and are only useful
through their identity. An [Object] instance is equal to itself
only.
children.name: Object

children.comment:
This is part of an implementation of the ImageBundle optimization implemented
with ClientBundle.
children.name: ImageResourcePrototype

children.comment: Only called by generated code.
children.name: ImageResourcePrototype

children.comment:
Indicates that an ImageResource should be bundled in such a way as to
support horizontal or vertical repetition.
children.name: RepeatStyle

children.comment: The image is not intended to be tiled.
children.name: None

children.comment: The image is intended to be tiled horizontally.
children.name: Horizontal

children.comment: The image is intended to be tiled vertically.
children.name: Vertical

children.comment:
The image is intended to be tiled both horizontally and vertically. Note
that this will prevent compositing of the particular image in most cases.
children.name: Both

children.comment: Specifies additional options to control how an image is bundled.
children.name: ImageOptions

children.comment: If true, the image will be flipped about the y-axis when {@link com.google.gwt.i18n.client.LocaleInfo#isRTL()} returns true. This is intended to be used by graphics that are sensitive to layout direction, such as arrows and disclosure indicators.
children.name: flipRtl

children.comment: Set to a positive value to override the image's intrinsic height. The image bundling code will scale the image to the desired height. If only one of width or height are set, the aspect ratio of the image will be maintained.
children.name: height

children.comment:
Set to {@code true} to require the ImageResource to be downloaded as a
separate resource at runtime. Specifically, this will disable the use of
{@code data:} URLs or other bundling optimizations for the image. This
can be used for infrequently-displayed images.
children.name: preventInlining

children.comment:
This option affects the image bundling optimization to allow the image to
be used with the {@link CssResource} {@code @sprite} rule where
repetition of the image is desired.

@see "CssResource documentation"
children.name: repeatStyle

children.comment: Set to a positive value to override the image's intrinsic width. The image bundling code will scale the image to the desired width. If only one of width or height are set, the aspect ratio of the image will be maintained.
children.name: width

children.comment: Provides access to image resources at runtime.
children.name: ImageResource

children.comment: Returns the height of the image.
children.name: height

children.comment: Returns the horizontal position of the image within the composite image.
children.name: left

children.comment: Returns the URL for the composite image that contains the ImageResource.
children.name: url

children.comment: Returns the vertical position of the image within the composite image.
children.name: top

children.comment: Returns the width of the image.
children.name: width

children.comment: Return true if the image contains multiple frames.
children.name: animated

children.comment: The base interface all bundle resource types must extend.
children.name: ResourcePrototype

children.comment:
Returns the name of the function within the ClientBundle used to create the
ResourcePrototype.

@return the name of the function within the ClientBundle used to create the
        ResourcePrototype
children.name: name

children.comment:
Specifies the classpath location of the resource or resources associated
with the {@link ResourcePrototype}.
children.name: Source

children.comment:
The use of this interface is similar to that of ImageBundle. Declare
no-argument functions that return subclasses of {@link ResourcePrototype},
which are annotated with {@link ClientBundle.Source} annotations specifying
the classpath location of the resource to include in the output. At runtime,
the functions will return an object that can be used to access the data in
the original resource.
children.name: ClientBundle
